534
00:32:06,508 --> 00:32:08,760
-No interest?
-None.

535
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:12,806
-He's good as a friend?
-He's good as a friend.

536
00:32:14,850 --> 00:32:16,893
You can't see him as anything more.

537
00:32:20,772 --> 00:32:22,065
It was...

538
00:32:24,443 --> 00:32:27,028
How should I put this?

539
00:32:27,821 --> 00:32:30,532
We couldn't talk much.

540
00:32:31,533 --> 00:32:33,535
Or, I mean...

541
00:32:34,620 --> 00:32:36,455
there was no time to talk.

542
00:32:37,205 --> 00:32:39,750
-None?
-Yeah, none.

543
00:32:39,833 --> 00:32:41,793
There must have been some.

544
00:32:41,877 --> 00:32:43,795
While we were in line for tickets,

545
00:32:43,879 --> 00:32:45,922
and a little during the previews,

546
00:32:46,006 --> 00:32:47,466
I tried to talk to her.

547
00:32:48,424 --> 00:32:49,968
What about during dinner?

548
00:32:50,051 --> 00:32:51,052
Dinner...

549
00:32:52,095 --> 00:32:55,348
She had plans with her grandma.

550
00:32:55,431 --> 00:32:56,558
-What?
-What?

551
00:32:56,642 --> 00:32:59,686
-Really?
-She said she does every Friday.

552
00:33:00,896 --> 00:33:02,355
I had forgotten.

553
00:33:03,273 --> 00:33:07,861
-I see.
-So I went to eat by myself.

554
00:33:09,571 --> 00:33:13,283
She does go every Friday, that's right.

555
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:15,536
-Totally forgot about that.
-Me, too.

556
00:33:15,619 --> 00:33:17,203
It was a surprise.

557
00:33:17,287 --> 00:33:21,542
-But did you ask her to dinner anyway?
-I did.

558
00:33:21,625 --> 00:33:24,044
And she said she can't
because of her grandma?

559
00:33:24,169 --> 00:33:26,213
Yeah, she apologized.

560
00:33:26,296 --> 00:33:27,923
But, actually...

561
00:33:29,049 --> 00:33:31,593
she cares about her family.

562
00:33:31,677 --> 00:33:34,012
And she should take care of her grandma.

563
00:33:35,722 --> 00:33:37,265
It can't be helped.

564
00:33:37,348 --> 00:33:39,225
-Yeah, it can't be helped.
-Yeah.

565
00:33:39,309 --> 00:33:41,436
Still, it must have been a shock.

566
00:33:41,520 --> 00:33:45,106
Yeah, it definitely got to me.

567
00:33:46,942 --> 00:33:50,361
It felt like she was just being nice.

568
00:33:50,445 --> 00:33:53,239
Like she came to be nice.

569
00:33:55,158 --> 00:34:00,581
It didn't feel right to me.
It felt uncomfortable.

570
00:34:00,664 --> 00:34:01,540
Yeah.

571
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:04,167
It was a really good experience.

572
00:34:05,168 --> 00:34:07,170
And Lauren...

573
00:34:07,253 --> 00:34:12,425
she's a really good person
for even coming with me.

574
00:34:14,302 --> 00:34:16,096
But for me...

575
00:34:17,222 --> 00:34:18,348
after today...

576
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:22,102
going out together made me think...

577
00:34:22,978 --> 00:34:25,480
that maybe we're not a good fit.

578
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:30,485
But you wouldn't have known that
without going on a date.

579
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:34,405
It's not something you'd know
from just hanging out at home.

580
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:36,032
I think it was good.

581
00:34:36,116 --> 00:34:40,662
So, what I'm thinking at this point...

582
00:34:41,788 --> 00:34:43,498
is that I'm going to give up.

583
00:34:45,709 --> 00:34:46,710
Yeah.

584
00:34:48,503 --> 00:34:52,132
If you're saying you want to give up,

585
00:34:53,508 --> 00:34:55,426
then you're free to do that.

586
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:59,765
If you say you want to try asking her
out again, then I'm here for you.

587
00:35:00,891 --> 00:35:02,601
I don't know...

588
00:35:03,602 --> 00:35:06,146
what'll happen in the future.

589
00:35:06,229 --> 00:35:07,480
But for now...

590
00:35:12,402 --> 00:35:13,403
I think...

591
00:35:16,031 --> 00:35:20,661
I should focus more on what I need to do
and what I'm working on now.

592
00:35:29,419 --> 00:35:33,006
There's something
that's been bothering me.

593
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:39,095
Everyone seems to have the wrong idea
about Yuya and me...

594
00:35:39,179 --> 00:35:40,722
and our relationship.

595
00:35:40,806 --> 00:35:46,102
It's true that, at first,
I was certainly interested in him.

596
00:35:47,688 --> 00:35:54,527
But the biggest reason for that
was because my last boyfriend of six years

597
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:56,529
had the exact same name.

598
00:35:56,612 --> 00:35:58,156
-Yuya?
-Yeah.

599
00:35:59,157 --> 00:36:03,453
And I used to call him Yuya-kun.

600
00:36:03,536 --> 00:36:08,499
I was drunk on the feeling
of calling him that.

601
00:36:09,375 --> 00:36:12,754
So I was interested,
but not because I liked him.

602
00:36:12,838 --> 00:36:16,591
I really think of him as a friend now.

603
00:36:16,675 --> 00:36:17,926
Yeah.

604
00:36:18,009 --> 00:36:24,015
I wanted to apologize,
if I made you feel uncomfortable...

605
00:36:24,099 --> 00:36:29,187
every time you were out
on a date with him.

606
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:34,442
I want you to go out with him
without worrying about anything.

607
00:36:34,525 --> 00:36:38,989
I'm not sure where you guys are at, but--

608
00:36:39,072 --> 00:36:42,743
-I'm glad you told me.
-Was it better I did?

609
00:36:42,826 --> 00:36:44,494
Yeah, it's better.

610
00:36:44,577 --> 00:36:45,661
Of course.

611
00:36:45,746 --> 00:36:49,249
I was really worried about it.

612
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:54,295
And I wanted to hear your thoughts, too.

613
00:36:54,379 --> 00:36:57,382
I was going to talk to you about it.

614
00:36:57,465 --> 00:36:59,384
I've wanted to tell you that.

615
00:37:00,093 --> 00:37:01,094
Thank you.

616
00:37:02,971 --> 00:37:05,766
-Oh, wow.
-Looks so good!

617
00:37:05,849 --> 00:37:06,850
Wow.

618
00:37:08,268 --> 00:37:10,270
Now, on to the main topic.

619
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:16,359
I'm leaving.

620
00:37:17,277 --> 00:37:18,611
What?

621
00:37:19,279 --> 00:37:20,280
You're kidding.

